    "updated_at": "2016-06-21T13:26:36Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Regular moves use a `nearEnough` parameter of 8, which causes bad behavior when units are ordered across bridges or other choke points.  `nearEnough` really needs to be ripped out and replaced with a smarter check for whether the unit has reached something close enough to its destination.  It would be worth checking how the original games handled this.\n"
